  "datePublished": "2026-04-27",
  "description": "Settlerism — settler colonialism understood as a continuing structure rather than a finished event — supplies the historical-material substrate the contemporary apparatus runs on. The genres in which subjects are formatted presuppose a settler-cultural imaginary, and the temporal middle is structurally eliminated by the binary the structure offers. The cybernetic subject is a settler subject in a specific structural sense, regardless of biographical specification.",
  "name": "Settlerism and the Cybernetic Subject",
